            "answer_text": "Interfacing a microprocessor is to connect it with various peripherals to perform various operations to obtain a desired output. Memory Interfacing and I/O Interfacing are the two main types of interfacing. Memory Interfacing is used when the microprocessor needs to access memory frequently for reading and writing data stored in the memory . It is used when reading/writing to a specific register of a memory chip. I/O Interfacing is achieved by connecting keyboard(input) and display monitors(output) with the microprocessor.   ",
